x4freetext: The reaction target was a 100 mu-m thick polypropylene
foil, (CH2)3.
The secondary beam was produced by fragmentation of a
75 MeV/nucleon 13C beam delivered by the GANIL
accelerator on a 1155 mg/cm 2 carbon production target,
located between the two superconducting solenoids of
the SISSI device. The secondary beam was analyzed by
the alpha spectrometer with a magnetic rigidity set at
2.82 Tm which corresponds to an average energy of
41.6 MeV/nucleon for the 6He ions.
All the scattered particles were unambiguously
identified in the focal plane of the spectromerer
with an ionisation chamber and a plastic scintillator.
The momentum and scattering angle were measured
with two position sensitive drift chambers placed 70 cm
apart and located near the focal plane
of the spectrometer.
Normalization uncertainty.
The absolute normalization for the elastic scattering
data on the protons in the (CH2)3 target was obtained
from the elastic scattering on 12C which was measured
simultaneously.
Experimental error
